metadata.name: Self-Awareness
metadata.description:
Overwhelmed... caught in an endless spiral of self-awareness.  I have spent years avoiding anything that caused discomfort, including addressing my own mind and mental health.  Now, diving deeper and deeper, it has uncovered even more anxiety, more stress and more self-doubt.  Is this really useful?  Maybe I should put all the trash back, bury it deep inside.  Maybe it's just time to say, "Fuck it, I'm me".
